==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mediocrity
<hw>Me`di*oc"ri*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧diocrit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, L.
<ets>mediocritas</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of being mediocre; a middle state or
degree; a moderate degree or rate.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>mediocrity</xex>
of success.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Moderation; temperance.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A mediocre person; -- used disparagingly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mediostapedial</ent>⟦br⟧
